  "body": "```\r\nclass App extends Component() {\r\n  fn1() {\r\n    this.setState({a});\r\n    fn2()\r\n  }\r\n  fn2() {\r\n    this.setState({b});\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nIs it guaranteed that calling `fn1` will only trigger a single re-render?\r\nIs it a better practise to pass `a` to `fn2` and keep it to a single `setState({a, b})` call?",
